I do it when I'm on the
phone with somebody.

00:40:47.180 --> 00:40:48.350 align:middle line:90%
I do it when I'm driving.

00:40:48.350 --> 00:40:50.023 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to--

00:40:50.023 --> 00:40:51.690 align:middle line:84%
you can still pay
attention to the road.

00:40:51.690 --> 00:40:52.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:40:52.190 --> 00:40:52.990 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:40:52.990 --> 00:40:54.650 align:middle line:84%
It would've been
perfect, this morning.

00:40:54.650 --> 00:40:57.710 align:middle line:84%
And I would love to have
a little more compassion,

00:40:57.710 --> 00:40:59.580 align:middle line:84%
for I had no idea what
he was going through.

00:40:59.580 --> 00:41:00.380 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah.

00:41:00.380 --> 00:41:03.068 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So to have
that anywhere, I mean,

00:41:03.068 --> 00:41:04.610 align:middle line:84%
imagine what this
world would be like

00:41:04.610 --> 00:41:06.650 align:middle line:90%
if we were all compassionate.

00:41:06.650 --> 00:41:07.700 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: Totally, if we were
all walking around feeling

00:41:07.700 --> 00:41:08.720 align:middle line:90%
more--

00:41:08.720 --> 00:41:10.650 align:middle line:84%
feeling our own
love and compassion.

00:41:10.650 --> 00:41:12.300 align:middle line:90%
Then, it changes everything.

00:41:12.300 --> 00:41:15.185 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then this
leads to the miracles.

00:41:15.185 --> 00:41:17.300 align:middle line:90%
What does miracle mean to you?

00:41:17.300 --> 00:41:18.750 align:middle line:90%
What is your definition of that?

00:41:18.750 --> 00:41:20.990 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: So the
dictionary definition,

00:41:20.990 --> 00:41:23.210 align:middle line:84%
Webster's definition
of a miracle,

00:41:23.210 --> 00:41:27.560 align:middle line:84%
is a surprise and
welcome event that

00:41:27.560 --> 00:41:31.970 align:middle line:84%
is not explainable by
science and that can often

00:41:31.970 --> 00:41:36.020 align:middle line:84%
be attributed to
grace or divine grace.

00:41:36.020 --> 00:41:37.980 align:middle line:90%
And so here's the deal.

00:41:37.980 --> 00:41:40.110 align:middle line:90%
We can't create miracles.

00:41:40.110 --> 00:41:44.600 align:middle line:84%
I believe that miracles
come to us from grace.

00:41:44.600 --> 00:41:47.600 align:middle line:84%
But what we can do is
we can put ourselves

00:41:47.600 --> 00:41:49.620 align:middle line:90%
in that flow of grace.

00:41:49.620 --> 00:41:52.850 align:middle line:84%
We can put ourselves in
the flow of miracles.

00:41:52.850 --> 00:41:55.680 align:middle line:84%
There's a great quote
by Sri Ramakrishna,

00:41:55.680 --> 00:41:58.830 align:middle line:84%
who said the winds of
grace are always blowing.

00:41:58.830 --> 00:42:01.040 align:middle line:90%
We have to raise our sales.

00:42:01.040 --> 00:42:02.917 align:middle line:90%
And that's what it is.

00:42:02.917 --> 00:42:05.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we teach
in Your Year of Miracles,

00:42:05.000 --> 00:42:08.330 align:middle line:84%
is we teach people how to
raise their sales to be

00:42:08.330 --> 00:42:09.950 align:middle line:90%
living in this miracle zone.

00:42:09.950 --> 00:42:12.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is it different
than intentions?

00:42:12.030 --> 00:42:13.150 align:middle line:90%


00:42:13.150 --> 00:42:15.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: It is,
to some degree.

00:42:15.620 --> 00:42:20.590 align:middle line:84%
Intention is part of it,
but it's more than that.

00:42:20.590 --> 00:42:22.700 align:middle line:84%
And maybe what we
can look at is,

00:42:22.700 --> 00:42:26.270 align:middle line:84%
what are the mistakes that
people make that keep them

00:42:26.270 --> 00:42:27.968 align:middle line:84%
from living more in
the miracle zone?

00:42:27.968 --> 00:42:29.510 align:middle line:84%
And then I'll share
with you what you

00:42:29.510 --> 00:42:31.115 align:middle line:90%
can do to write those mistakes.

00:42:31.115 --> 00:42:32.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because I'm
thinking, Marci, of times

00:42:32.990 --> 00:42:34.000 align:middle line:90%
where I need a miracle.

00:42:34.000 --> 00:42:34.800 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah.

00:42:34.800 --> 00:42:37.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Like, I need a
straight-up Hail Mary.

00:42:37.100 --> 00:42:39.440 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah, and a lot
of people feel that way.

00:42:39.440 --> 00:42:41.706 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, yeah.

00:42:41.706 --> 00:42:44.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: And I
understand that deeply.

00:42:44.610 --> 00:42:47.060 align:middle line:84%
And I know that
any of the things

00:42:47.060 --> 00:42:50.690 align:middle line:84%
that we're going to talk about,
they put you more in that state

00:42:50.690 --> 00:42:52.670 align:middle line:84%
where the miracle,
you'll see the miracle.

00:42:52.670 --> 00:42:53.480 align:middle line:90%
It'll show up more.

00:42:53.480 --> 00:42:55.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's creating
the environment for it.

00:42:55.010 --> 00:42:56.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: That's right.

00:42:56.010 --> 00:42:59.030 align:middle line:84%
So number one, one of the
biggest mistakes people make

00:42:59.030 --> 00:43:01.140 align:middle line:90%
is they hold on.

00:43:01.140 --> 00:43:04.430 align:middle line:84%
They hold onto the past,
and they don't let go.

00:43:04.430 --> 00:43:07.850 align:middle line:84%
And when we don't let go,
the universe cannot come

00:43:07.850 --> 00:43:11.630 align:middle line:84%
in and give us
what it is we want.

00:43:11.630 --> 00:43:12.650 align:middle line:90%
We can't get the new.

00:43:12.650 --> 00:43:16.580 align:middle line:84%
You know, there's a saying,
nature abhors a vacuum.

00:43:16.580 --> 00:43:22.280 align:middle line:84%
So when you're filled with old
stuff, old thoughts, old stuff

00:43:22.280 --> 00:43:24.710 align:middle line:84%
that you're hanging
onto, the universe

00:43:24.710 --> 00:43:26.960 align:middle line:84%
will not bring in
miracles for you.

00:43:26.960 --> 00:43:29.565 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm going to give
you a simple practice.

00:43:29.565 --> 00:43:30.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, I love it.

00:43:30.990 --> 00:43:33.830 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: To get you in
the habit of letting go.

00:43:33.830 --> 00:43:36.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, because that
pattern of neural grooves,

00:43:36.830 --> 00:43:39.310 align:middle line:84%
talk about creating
patterns of negativity.

00:43:39.310 --> 00:43:40.400 align:middle line:90%
It drives deep.

00:43:40.400 --> 00:43:41.870 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: It does drive deep.

00:43:41.870 --> 00:43:43.670 align:middle line:84%
And I was not a
good letter goer.

00:43:43.670 --> 00:43:45.200 align:middle line:90%
I was a hanger-oner.

00:43:45.200 --> 00:43:47.060 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm going
to start you off

00:43:47.060 --> 00:43:50.090 align:middle line:84%
on letting go of
some physical stuff

00:43:50.090 --> 00:43:52.580 align:middle line:84%
because that helps you
let go emotionally.

00:43:52.580 --> 00:43:54.060 align:middle line:90%
It gets you trained to let go.

00:43:54.060 --> 00:43:54.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:43:54.860 --> 00:43:55.850 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: And the
practice that I'm

00:43:55.850 --> 00:43:57.308 align:middle line:84%
going to share with
you is called--

00:43:57.308 --> 00:43:58.430 align:middle line:90%
is a feng shui practice.

00:43:58.430 --> 00:44:00.090 align:middle line:84%
I learned it from
a feng shui master.

00:44:00.090 --> 00:44:03.710 align:middle line:84%
Feng shui is the Chinese
art of placement and flow,

00:44:03.710 --> 00:44:06.560 align:middle line:84%
how to create placement
in your home for flow.

00:44:06.560 --> 00:44:09.950 align:middle line:84%
And it's simply,
I call it 27 by 9.

00:44:09.950 --> 00:44:14.390 align:middle line:84%
You give away 27 items a
day for nine days in a row.

00:44:14.390 --> 00:44:19.030 align:middle line:84%
You give away or throw away
27 items a day for nine days.

00:44:19.030 --> 00:44:21.090 align:middle line:84%
And you think, I
don't have 27 items I

00:44:21.090 --> 00:44:22.340 align:middle line:90%
could give away or throw away.

00:44:22.340 --> 00:44:22.775 align:middle line:90%
You do.

00:44:22.775 --> 00:44:23.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You do.

00:44:23.420 --> 00:44:24.220 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: You do.

00:44:24.220 --> 00:44:26.750 align:middle line:84%
You will be amazed how
many like broken pens

00:44:26.750 --> 00:44:28.880 align:middle line:84%
you have and all
kinds of things.

00:44:28.880 --> 00:44:32.180 align:middle line:84%
And you don't skip a day because
each day it's cumulative.

00:44:32.180 --> 00:44:34.720 align:middle line:90%
Each day builds on the last day.

00:44:34.720 --> 00:44:39.950 align:middle line:84%
And miracles happen at
the end of the nine days.

00:44:39.950 --> 00:44:43.190 align:middle line:84%
People have jobs-- job
offers come to them

00:44:43.190 --> 00:44:44.528 align:middle line:90%
that they've wanted for years.

00:44:44.528 --> 00:44:45.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Create the space.

00:44:45.570 --> 00:44:47.237 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: They meet
their life partner.

00:44:47.237 --> 00:44:49.502 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's uncanny
what happens.

00:44:49.502 --> 00:44:50.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's awesome.

00:44:50.460 --> 00:44:51.560 align:middle line:90%
That's awesome.

00:44:51.560 --> 00:44:53.370 align:middle line:90%
And all of that holds energy.

00:44:53.370 --> 00:44:54.170 align:middle line:90%
It keeps us--

00:44:54.170 --> 00:44:55.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: It does.

00:44:55.140 --> 00:44:55.940 align:middle line:90%
It does.

00:44:55.940 --> 00:44:58.290 align:middle line:90%
And so you're saying, I'm ready.

00:44:58.290 --> 00:44:59.150 align:middle line:90%
I'm willing.

00:44:59.150 --> 00:45:00.980 align:middle line:84%
I'm letting go of
that old stuff.

00:45:00.980 --> 00:45:01.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Releasing it.

00:45:01.970 --> 00:45:03.090 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Releasing it.

00:45:03.090 --> 00:45:05.035 align:middle line:84%
And when you do
that, you also start

00:45:05.035 --> 00:45:07.160 align:middle line:84%
to be able to release some
of the emotional baggage

00:45:07.160 --> 00:45:07.760 align:middle line:90%
that we carry.

00:45:07.760 --> 00:45:09.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, and
you create space.

00:45:09.140 --> 00:45:09.770 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: That's right.

00:45:09.770 --> 00:45:11.145 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I'm thinking
of 27 things

00:45:11.145 --> 00:45:12.290 align:middle line:90%
I can let go of right now.

00:45:12.290 --> 00:45:13.040 align:middle line:90%
I'm gonna get a box.

00:45:13.040 --> 00:45:13.910 align:middle line:90%
I'm gonna put it all in there.

00:45:13.910 --> 00:45:16.035 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: And some of it
you're going to put away,

00:45:16.035 --> 00:45:19.010 align:middle line:84%
and some of them
you're going to donate.

00:45:19.010 --> 00:45:22.370 align:middle line:90%
It feels so extraordinary.

00:45:22.370 --> 00:45:25.040 align:middle line:84%
A number of years ago, there
was a great book called

00:45:25.040 --> 00:45:26.780 align:middle line:90%
"The Magic Art of Tidying Up."

00:45:26.780 --> 00:45:28.690 align:middle line:84%
And it was based on
that same principle.

00:45:28.690 --> 00:45:29.770 align:middle line:90%
But this is simple.

00:45:29.770 --> 00:45:33.615 align:middle line:84%
27 items for nine days,
and then watch your life

00:45:33.615 --> 00:45:34.490 align:middle line:90%
and see what happens.

00:45:34.490 --> 00:45:36.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Have you ever moved
and you can't understand

00:45:36.800 --> 00:45:38.000 align:middle line:90%
how you have so much stuff?

00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:39.000 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah, I know.

00:45:39.000 --> 00:45:41.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And it multiplies.

00:45:41.040 --> 00:45:43.370 align:middle line:84%
And, yes, things
that we don't let

00:45:43.370 --> 00:45:44.870 align:middle line:84%
go of that are no
longer working,

00:45:44.870 --> 00:45:46.370 align:middle line:84%
that are broken,
that someday you'll

00:45:46.370 --> 00:45:48.590 align:middle line:84%
fix, or stain on the
shirt, and all of that.

00:45:48.590 --> 00:45:50.630 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it creates this space.

00:45:50.630 --> 00:45:54.410 align:middle line:84%
I used to do this on my
desk and cleared the desk.

00:45:54.410 --> 00:45:56.810 align:middle line:84%
And every time I did that,
a new job would come--

00:45:56.810 --> 00:45:57.635 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah.

00:45:57.635 --> 00:45:58.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And then, I forgot.

00:45:58.760 --> 00:45:59.940 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah.

00:45:59.940 --> 00:46:03.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Something that was
rewarding and validating,

00:46:03.520 --> 00:46:04.320 align:middle line:90%
I would remember.

00:46:04.320 --> 00:46:05.700 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: It puts
you in the zone,

00:46:05.700 --> 00:46:06.820 align:middle line:90%
puts you in the miracle zone.

00:46:06.820 --> 00:46:07.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's the miracle zone.

00:46:07.730 --> 00:46:09.188 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: That's
the miracle zone.

00:46:09.188 --> 00:46:10.620 align:middle line:90%
And here's another one.

00:46:10.620 --> 00:46:12.430 align:middle line:84%
I want to give you
some practical stuff.

00:46:12.430 --> 00:46:13.920 align:middle line:84%
You and I, we love
the practical.

00:46:13.920 --> 00:46:14.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We do.

00:46:14.250 --> 00:46:15.050 align:middle line:90%
We do.

00:46:15.050 --> 00:46:17.230 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: So when
people ask me,

00:46:17.230 --> 00:46:19.210 align:middle line:84%
what's the biggest thing
that keeps people out

00:46:19.210 --> 00:46:22.930 align:middle line:84%
of the miracle zone, I
would say the answer is,

00:46:22.930 --> 00:46:26.220 align:middle line:90%
lack of self-love.

00:46:26.220 --> 00:46:29.560 align:middle line:84%
When we don't love
ourselves enough,

00:46:29.560 --> 00:46:31.840 align:middle line:84%
we don't feel
worthy of miracles,

00:46:31.840 --> 00:46:34.180 align:middle line:90%
and we push them away.

00:46:34.180 --> 00:46:36.370 align:middle line:84%
They're there, and we're
going-- subconsciously,

00:46:36.370 --> 00:46:37.810 align:middle line:84%
we're not doing
this consciously.

00:46:37.810 --> 00:46:40.375 align:middle line:84%
But, subconsciously,
we're going, no, no, no.

00:46:40.375 --> 00:46:42.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: As women,
we tend to also want

00:46:42.910 --> 00:46:43.880 align:middle line:90%
to play small and hide.

00:46:43.880 --> 00:46:44.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: That's right.

00:46:44.470 --> 00:46:45.190 align:middle line:90%
That's exactly right.

00:46:45.190 --> 00:46:46.148 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But we're here.

00:46:46.148 --> 00:46:47.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Exactly.

00:46:47.590 --> 00:46:52.330 align:middle line:84%
You know, think about ways
that you-- and unconsciously

00:46:52.330 --> 00:46:55.690 align:middle line:84%
are pushing away good
in your life, daily.

00:46:55.690 --> 00:46:58.990 align:middle line:84%
Things like, people give you a
compliment, you push it away.

00:46:58.990 --> 00:47:01.400 align:middle line:84%
People offer you support,
and you feel like,

00:47:01.400 --> 00:47:03.505 align:middle line:84%
oh, no, I've got to help
them twice as much as--

00:47:03.505 --> 00:47:04.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I don't deserve it.

00:47:04.630 --> 00:47:05.950 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: I don't deserve it.

00:47:05.950 --> 00:47:07.780 align:middle line:84%
Or we feel like if
good comes our way,

00:47:07.780 --> 00:47:10.030 align:middle line:84%
we feel guilty because we
feel like we should have

00:47:10.030 --> 00:47:11.850 align:middle line:90%
had to work harder to get it.

00:47:11.850 --> 00:47:13.600 align:middle line:84%
You know, all of these
are ways that we're

00:47:13.600 --> 00:47:17.470 align:middle line:90%
pushing away our good.

00:47:17.470 --> 00:47:19.810 align:middle line:84%
And so what we want
to do is open up

00:47:19.810 --> 00:47:23.800 align:middle line:84%
to self-love to feel
more worthy of it.

00:47:23.800 --> 00:47:26.210 align:middle line:84%
And I'll tell you in a
minute what I do for that,

00:47:26.210 --> 00:47:30.910 align:middle line:84%
but I want to tell you a quick
story that really shifted

00:47:30.910 --> 00:47:32.570 align:middle line:90%
things for me around this.

00:47:32.570 --> 00:47:33.560 align:middle line:90%
And it's around money.

00:47:33.560 --> 00:47:37.300 align:middle line:84%
I know that a lot of people
want to receive more money.

00:47:37.300 --> 00:47:40.000 align:middle line:90%
They want more money, right?

00:47:40.000 --> 00:47:44.810 align:middle line:84%
And I remember years ago,
probably 20 years ago,

00:47:44.810 --> 00:47:47.480 align:middle line:84%
I went to a workshop
with Marianne Williamson,

00:47:47.480 --> 00:47:51.340 align:middle line:84%
who is an extraordinary--
she's now a dear friend--

00:47:51.340 --> 00:47:55.270 align:middle line:84%
she's just an extraordinary
teacher, and woman, and person.

00:47:55.270 --> 00:48:01.360 align:middle line:84%
And she said that if you
start making a lot of money

00:48:01.360 --> 00:48:04.360 align:middle line:84%
and you don't raise your
consciousness, if you don't

00:48:04.360 --> 00:48:07.150 align:middle line:84%
have that feeling of
worthiness, if you

00:48:07.150 --> 00:48:10.180 align:middle line:84%
don't raise your consciousness,
you will inevitably lose it.

00:48:10.180 --> 00:48:12.520 align:middle line:90%
And I remember thinking, no way.

00:48:12.520 --> 00:48:13.960 align:middle line:90%
That will never happen to me.

00:48:13.960 --> 00:48:16.760 align:middle line:84%
If I started making a lot
of money, I won't lose that.

00:48:16.760 --> 00:48:18.280 align:middle line:84%
Well, sure enough,
a year later, I

00:48:18.280 --> 00:48:20.590 align:middle line:84%
started making a
lot of money, way

00:48:20.590 --> 00:48:23.582 align:middle line:84%
more than what my
consciousness felt worthy of.

00:48:23.582 --> 00:48:24.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Your set point.

00:48:24.540 --> 00:48:25.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Exactly.

00:48:25.340 --> 00:48:27.370 align:middle line:84%
I hit my upper
limit, my set point,

00:48:27.370 --> 00:48:29.200 align:middle line:90%
and I started losing money.

00:48:29.200 --> 00:48:32.380 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, I was losing
it in all kinds of ways.

00:48:32.380 --> 00:48:35.710 align:middle line:84%
Now, fortunately, I remembered
what Marianne had said.

00:48:35.710 --> 00:48:38.280 align:middle line:84%
And I started working
on that consciousness,

00:48:38.280 --> 00:48:42.580 align:middle line:84%
on that self-love that felt
worthy of receiving it.

00:48:42.580 --> 00:48:44.590 align:middle line:90%
And so I turned it around.

00:48:44.590 --> 00:48:46.330 align:middle line:84%
And so I say to
people, when you're

00:48:46.330 --> 00:48:50.210 align:middle line:84%
saying, I want more
of this or that, ask,

00:48:50.210 --> 00:48:51.970 align:middle line:90%
do I have that worthiness?

00:48:51.970 --> 00:48:53.725 align:middle line:84%
Do I have that deep
feeling of self-love?

00:48:53.725 --> 00:48:55.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That makes
so much sense.

00:48:55.120 --> 00:48:57.370 align:middle line:84%
Because people see you the
way that you see yourself.

00:48:57.370 --> 00:48:58.030 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: That's right.

00:48:58.030 --> 00:48:59.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if you're
showing up in a room

00:48:59.770 --> 00:49:01.623 align:middle line:84%
playing small, and
not feeling worthy,

00:49:01.623 --> 00:49:03.040 align:middle line:84%
and not having a
lot of self-love,

00:49:03.040 --> 00:49:04.450 align:middle line:84%
that's how you
will be perceived.

00:49:04.450 --> 00:49:06.920 align:middle line:84%
And then we wonder, well,
they don't see my value.

00:49:06.920 --> 00:49:10.728 align:middle line:84%
But if you turn that around
and have the practice first--

00:49:10.728 --> 00:49:11.770 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: That's right--

00:49:11.770 --> 00:49:12.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --raising
your consciousness,

00:49:12.970 --> 00:49:13.690 align:middle line:90%
raising the self--

00:49:13.690 --> 00:49:15.010 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: And I
think the universe,

00:49:15.010 --> 00:49:16.810 align:middle line:84%
it said that people
won't give to you more

00:49:16.810 --> 00:49:18.130 align:middle line:90%
than what you feel worthy of.

00:49:18.130 --> 00:49:20.080 align:middle line:84%
I believe the universe
is the same way.

00:49:20.080 --> 00:49:22.390 align:middle line:84%
The universe will
not give to you

00:49:22.390 --> 00:49:24.160 align:middle line:90%
beyond what you feel worthy of.

00:49:24.160 --> 00:49:26.295 align:middle line:84%
So we've got to
develop some self-love.

00:49:26.295 --> 00:49:27.170 align:middle line:90%
So how do we do that?

00:49:27.170 --> 00:49:28.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, it's that
responsibility thing, too.

00:49:28.570 --> 00:49:29.820 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah, that's right.

00:49:29.820 --> 00:49:32.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Taking responsibility
for feeling worthy,

00:49:32.500 --> 00:49:34.240 align:middle line:90%
loved, compassionate.

00:49:34.240 --> 00:49:35.222 align:middle line:90%
Showing up that way,

00:49:35.222 --> 00:49:37.430 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah, and then
watch what the energy does.

00:49:37.430 --> 00:49:38.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:49:38.230 --> 00:49:41.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: OK, So simple
practice, and it's--

00:49:41.770 --> 00:49:44.100 align:middle line:84%
when we love something,
we take care of it, right?

00:49:44.100 --> 00:49:44.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:49:44.370 --> 00:49:45.820 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: You know, you
take care of things--

00:49:45.820 --> 00:49:48.250 align:middle line:84%
but what we don't do is we
don't take care of ourselves.

00:49:48.250 --> 00:49:51.950 align:middle line:84%
We're sending a message that
we're not worthy of that.

00:49:51.950 --> 00:49:54.520 align:middle line:84%
So what I want you
to do is ask yourself

00:49:54.520 --> 00:49:57.273 align:middle line:84%
this question a couple of
times a day, a simple question,

00:49:57.273 --> 00:49:58.690 align:middle line:84%
even write it on
a little Post-It.

00:49:58.690 --> 00:50:01.090 align:middle line:84%
Question is, what's
the most loving thing I

00:50:01.090 --> 00:50:03.700 align:middle line:90%
could do for myself right now?

00:50:03.700 --> 00:50:08.230 align:middle line:84%
What's the most loving thing I
could do for myself right now?

00:50:08.230 --> 00:50:10.270 align:middle line:84%
And then you stop,
and you do it.

00:50:10.270 --> 00:50:12.130 align:middle line:84%
It could be, I could
take some water.

00:50:12.130 --> 00:50:13.660 align:middle line:84%
It could be, I
could call a friend.

00:50:13.660 --> 00:50:16.060 align:middle line:84%
It could be, I could do
that inner ease technique.

00:50:16.060 --> 00:50:18.160 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
what the answer is.

00:50:18.160 --> 00:50:20.800 align:middle line:84%
What matters is your
training yourself

00:50:20.800 --> 00:50:22.955 align:middle line:90%
to take care of yourself.

00:50:22.955 --> 00:50:25.330 align:middle line:84%
And it shows yourself that
you're being more self-loving.

00:50:25.330 --> 00:50:26.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love that.

00:50:26.530 --> 00:50:27.940 align:middle line:84%
It sends the
message to yourself.

00:50:27.940 --> 00:50:29.222 align:middle line:90%
And it's small things.

00:50:29.222 --> 00:50:30.680 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
do anything huge.

00:50:30.680 --> 00:50:33.880 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: No, you're not going
to go out and save the world.

00:50:33.880 --> 00:50:36.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, you're just doing
small things to give, give,

00:50:36.870 --> 00:50:38.530 align:middle line:90%
give back to yourself.

00:50:38.530 --> 00:50:41.170 align:middle line:84%
And then it tells the
brain, the psyche.

00:50:41.170 --> 00:50:42.430 align:middle line:90%
I'm worth that.

00:50:42.430 --> 00:50:44.950 align:middle line:90%
I'm taking care of.

00:50:44.950 --> 00:50:49.000 align:middle line:84%
One of the most primal
human needs is to feel safe

00:50:49.000 --> 00:50:50.620 align:middle line:90%
and to feel loved.

00:50:50.620 --> 00:50:52.183 align:middle line:84%
Those two things
go hand in hand.

00:50:52.183 --> 00:50:54.100 align:middle line:84%
And when you do little
micro things like that,

00:50:54.100 --> 00:50:55.195 align:middle line:90%
it makes a lot of sense.

00:50:55.195 --> 00:50:56.190 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: It does.

00:50:56.190 --> 00:50:56.990 align:middle line:90%
It does.

00:50:56.990 --> 00:50:57.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love it.

00:50:57.700 --> 00:50:59.283 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: You know,
I want to go back

00:50:59.283 --> 00:51:01.375 align:middle line:84%
to our conversation
about what is a miracle.

00:51:01.375 --> 00:51:02.175 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:02.175 --> 00:51:06.140 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: Because
miracles can be anything.

00:51:06.140 --> 00:51:09.770 align:middle line:84%
It could be, you pick up
a book, and it has in it

00:51:09.770 --> 00:51:12.050 align:middle line:84%
exactly what it was you
needed to hear right then.

00:51:12.050 --> 00:51:12.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:12.850 --> 00:51:15.490 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: It could be the
person calls you on the phone

00:51:15.490 --> 00:51:18.560 align:middle line:84%
that has your answer or
that you needed to talk to--

00:51:18.560 --> 00:51:22.280 align:middle line:84%
small miracles all day long,
just that feeling-- the parking

00:51:22.280 --> 00:51:23.630 align:middle line:90%
place shows up.

00:51:23.630 --> 00:51:25.340 align:middle line:90%
Synchronicity.

00:51:25.340 --> 00:51:27.260 align:middle line:90%
Then, there are big miracles.

00:51:27.260 --> 00:51:29.520 align:middle line:90%
The big miracles.

00:51:29.520 --> 00:51:32.210 align:middle line:90%
Finding your soul mate.

00:51:32.210 --> 00:51:33.950 align:middle line:84%
We had so many
people that I know

00:51:33.950 --> 00:51:37.010 align:middle line:84%
that we have trained
these things, to move

00:51:37.010 --> 00:51:39.487 align:middle line:84%
into the miracle zone,
they've learned these things.

00:51:39.487 --> 00:51:41.570 align:middle line:84%
And they've been trying
to get pregnant for years,

00:51:41.570 --> 00:51:43.110 align:middle line:90%
and they suddenly get pregnant.

00:51:43.110 --> 00:51:43.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:51:43.910 --> 00:51:46.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: Or their
ideal job shows up,

00:51:46.520 --> 00:51:48.920 align:middle line:84%
or money comes in the mail
that they weren't expecting.

00:51:48.920 --> 00:51:52.160 align:middle line:84%
They needed that $3,000
to pay off something,

00:51:52.160 --> 00:51:54.690 align:middle line:84%
and it just showed up
exactly when they needed it.

00:51:54.690 --> 00:51:57.207 align:middle line:90%
There's even a story that--

00:51:57.207 --> 00:51:59.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I mean, do you
have to graduate into this?

00:51:59.540 --> 00:52:01.925 align:middle line:84%
Like, miracles are accessible
to everyone, right?

00:52:01.925 --> 00:52:03.200 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: They are.

00:52:03.200 --> 00:52:05.030 align:middle line:90%
They're accessible to everybody.

00:52:05.030 --> 00:52:07.790 align:middle line:90%
They're around us all day long.

00:52:07.790 --> 00:52:11.640 align:middle line:84%
It's up to us to put
ourselves in that space.

00:52:11.640 --> 00:52:13.460 align:middle line:84%
And then there's
extreme stories, like,

00:52:13.460 --> 00:52:15.770 align:middle line:90%
the Marcel Sternberger story.

00:52:15.770 --> 00:52:16.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes, Marcel.

00:52:16.940 --> 00:52:18.357 align:middle line:84%
I want you to
actually take a look

00:52:18.357 --> 00:52:20.150 align:middle line:84%
at this wonderful
video of her talking

00:52:20.150 --> 00:52:21.885 align:middle line:84%
about a miracle
in someone's life.

00:52:21.885 --> 00:52:22.685 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:52:22.685 --> 00:52:25.250 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: Hi,
I'm Marci Shimoff.

00:52:25.250 --> 00:52:27.920 align:middle line:84%
And welcome to our
happiness community.

00:52:27.920 --> 00:52:31.100 align:middle line:10%
I want to talk with you today
about a really cool subject--

00:52:31.100 --> 00:52:32.750 align:middle line:10%
miracles.

00:52:32.750 --> 00:52:34.763 align:middle line:10%
Now some of you know
that I have gotten

00:52:34.763 --> 00:52:36.680 align:middle line:10%
to co-author a number
of books in the "Chicken

00:52:36.680 --> 00:52:38.450 align:middle line:10%
Soup for the Soul"
series, and I've

00:52:38.450 --> 00:52:41.465 align:middle line:10%
been very fortunate to read
over 20,000 stories that

00:52:41.465 --> 00:52:43.340 align:middle line:10%
have been submitted to
the Chicken Soup books

00:52:43.340 --> 00:52:44.780 align:middle line:10%
over the years.

00:52:44.780 --> 00:52:48.920 align:middle line:10%
And I have read so many stories
about incredible, incredible

00:52:48.920 --> 00:52:50.090 align:middle line:10%
miracles.

00:52:50.090 --> 00:52:53.660 align:middle line:10%
So let me share with you
today one of my favorites.

00:52:53.660 --> 00:52:54.770 align:middle line:10%
It's really quite amazing.

00:52:54.770 --> 00:52:57.380 align:middle line:10%
It's a story about a man
named Marcel Sternberger.

00:52:57.380 --> 00:53:01.520 align:middle line:10%
And Marcel was
living in New York.

00:53:01.520 --> 00:53:05.540 align:middle line:10%
And he boarded everyday the
same subway, his 909 subway

00:53:05.540 --> 00:53:07.760 align:middle line:10%
into work.

00:53:07.760 --> 00:53:10.890 align:middle line:10%
And this one day, he ended
up taking a different subway.

00:53:10.890 --> 00:53:14.210 align:middle line:10%
And he gets on,
and there he sees--

00:53:14.210 --> 00:53:18.920 align:middle line:10%
he sits down next to a man who's
reading a Hungarian newspaper.

00:53:18.920 --> 00:53:21.980 align:middle line:10%
And Marcel was from Hungary.

00:53:21.980 --> 00:53:26.420 align:middle line:10%
And so he looked at the man and
he said, where are you from?

00:53:26.420 --> 00:53:27.710 align:middle line:10%
And what brought you here?

00:53:27.710 --> 00:53:30.990 align:middle line:10%
And the man said,
well, I was in Hungary,

00:53:30.990 --> 00:53:34.940 align:middle line:10%
and I had, really, to
escape the country.

00:53:34.940 --> 00:53:36.920 align:middle line:10%
And it was very sad.

00:53:36.920 --> 00:53:40.220 align:middle line:10%
I left my wife and the
rest of my family behind.

00:53:40.220 --> 00:53:42.020 align:middle line:10%
And they were all killed.

00:53:42.020 --> 00:53:44.900 align:middle line:10%
I went back to our village,
and really nobody was left,

00:53:44.900 --> 00:53:48.590 align:middle line:10%
and I came to America
about a year ago.

00:53:48.590 --> 00:53:52.020 align:middle line:10%
And at hearing this,
Marcel thought, wow,

00:53:52.020 --> 00:53:53.780 align:middle line:10%
this sounds really familiar.

00:53:53.780 --> 00:53:56.840 align:middle line:10%
About a week ago, he had been
at a party of some friends.

00:53:56.840 --> 00:53:59.030 align:middle line:10%
And he had heard a
very similar story

00:53:59.030 --> 00:54:01.850 align:middle line:10%
with the same village
even involved.

00:54:01.850 --> 00:54:05.270 align:middle line:10%
And he looked at the man and
he said, what's your name?

00:54:05.270 --> 00:54:08.420 align:middle line:10%
And the man said, well,
my name's Bela Paskin.

00:54:08.420 --> 00:54:11.830 align:middle line:10%
And the man said, what
was your wife's name?

00:54:11.830 --> 00:54:14.510 align:middle line:10%
And he said, well,
my wife, she's dead.

00:54:14.510 --> 00:54:16.760 align:middle line:10%
But it was Maria.

00:54:16.760 --> 00:54:21.123 align:middle line:10%
And Marcel took the man by
his hand and said, come on,

00:54:21.123 --> 00:54:22.790 align:middle line:10%
we have to get off
the train right away.

00:54:22.790 --> 00:54:24.150 align:middle line:10%
I have to make a phone call.

00:54:24.150 --> 00:54:26.660 align:middle line:10%
And they get off the
train, and he calls up

00:54:26.660 --> 00:54:29.390 align:middle line:10%
this phone number of this
woman he had met at a party

00:54:29.390 --> 00:54:30.880 align:middle line:10%
the prior week.

00:54:30.880 --> 00:54:32.630 align:middle line:10%
He gets on the phone
with her and he says,

00:54:32.630 --> 00:54:34.980 align:middle line:10%
what was your husband's name?

00:54:34.980 --> 00:54:37.800 align:middle line:10%
And she said, well,
my husband, he's dead,

00:54:37.800 --> 00:54:40.280 align:middle line:10%
but his name was Bela Paskin.

00:54:40.280 --> 00:54:46.870 align:middle line:10%
Marcel hands the phone to Bela
and said, this is a miracle.

00:54:46.870 --> 00:54:49.090 align:middle line:10%
This is your wife
on the other line.

00:54:49.090 --> 00:54:52.060 align:middle line:10%
Please tell her hello.

00:54:52.060 --> 00:54:55.510 align:middle line:10%
It happened on a
Brooklyn subway.

00:54:55.510 --> 00:54:57.670 align:middle line:10%
I've told this story
many times and I still

00:54:57.670 --> 00:55:00.280 align:middle line:10%
get goose bumps telling it.

00:55:00.280 --> 00:55:04.960 align:middle line:10%
Miracles can happen in our
life when we are open to them.

00:55:04.960 --> 00:55:07.120 align:middle line:10%
And you know, most
of us don't have

00:55:07.120 --> 00:55:09.940 align:middle line:10%
miracles like that
happening regularly,

00:55:09.940 --> 00:55:14.360 align:middle line:10%
but we have simple,
everyday miracles happening.

00:55:14.360 --> 00:55:17.500 align:middle line:10%
So what I invite you
to do in your own life,

00:55:17.500 --> 00:55:20.800 align:middle line:10%
right now, today, and
over the next week or so,

00:55:20.800 --> 00:55:24.350 align:middle line:10%
notice the miracles that
are happening in your life.

00:55:24.350 --> 00:55:28.420 align:middle line:10%
Notice the little ones and give
gratitude for the little ones.

00:55:28.420 --> 00:55:31.430 align:middle line:10%
Because when you do give
gratitude for those,

00:55:31.430 --> 00:55:33.650 align:middle line:10%
then the big ones
begin to show up.

00:55:33.650 --> 00:55:36.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That story about
Marcel is incredible.

00:55:36.700 --> 00:55:37.970 align:middle line:90%
It's so beautiful.

00:55:37.970 --> 00:55:42.430 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that he was
just able to create that

00:55:42.430 --> 00:55:44.290 align:middle line:90%
without ever even expecting it--

00:55:44.290 --> 00:55:47.620 align:middle line:84%
what you're saying is,
anyone can do this.

00:55:47.620 --> 00:55:51.190 align:middle line:84%
It's micro-miracles when
you start to look for them,

00:55:51.190 --> 00:55:54.430 align:middle line:84%
and then you kind of evolve
into these major miracles.

00:55:54.430 --> 00:55:55.690 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: That's right.

00:55:55.690 --> 00:55:57.850 align:middle line:84%
You know, there's this
principle that what

00:55:57.850 --> 00:56:01.460 align:middle line:84%
you put your attention on
grows stronger in your life.

00:56:01.460 --> 00:56:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And when you put
your attention on,

00:56:03.190 --> 00:56:04.960 align:middle line:84%
what are the
miracles showing up,

00:56:04.960 --> 00:56:06.675 align:middle line:90%
you start to get more of them.

00:56:06.675 --> 00:56:08.050 align:middle line:84%
So that's one
thing for everybody

00:56:08.050 --> 00:56:10.960 align:middle line:84%
to start to do, just
throughout your day, notice

00:56:10.960 --> 00:56:12.160 align:middle line:90%
what are the miracles.

00:56:12.160 --> 00:56:15.040 align:middle line:84%
Same thing we talked about with
happiness looking for the good.

00:56:15.040 --> 00:56:18.493 align:middle line:84%
Really register, wow, that was
miraculous what happened today.

00:56:18.493 --> 00:56:19.660 align:middle line:90%
And this is great awareness.

00:56:19.660 --> 00:56:21.202 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now you
talked about mistakes

00:56:21.202 --> 00:56:24.940 align:middle line:84%
people make to prevent
themselves and letting go,

00:56:24.940 --> 00:56:25.870 align:middle line:90%
which we talked about.

00:56:25.870 --> 00:56:26.500 align:middle line:90%
>>SHIMOFF: Yeah, not letting go.

00:56:26.500 --> 00:56:27.730 align:middle line:90%
They hang on too long.

00:56:27.730 --> 00:56:29.860 align:middle line:84%
We talked about, they don't
have enough self-love.

00:56:29.860 --> 00:56:31.730 align:middle line:90%
So two more mistakes.

00:56:31.730 --> 00:56:35.780 align:middle line:84%
One of them is, they
picture the wrong things.

00:56:35.780 --> 00:56:38.170 align:middle line:84%
They use the power
of their minds

00:56:38.170 --> 00:56:42.040 align:middle line:84%
to visualize exactly what they
don't want to have happen.

00:56:42.040 --> 00:56:43.060 align:middle line:90%
And that's called worry.

00:56:43.060 --> 00:56:44.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Another default.

00:56:44.060 --> 00:56:46.405 align:middle line:84%
>>SHIMOFF: Any time that
we're stuck in worry,

00:56:46.405 --> 00:56:49.330 align:middle line:84%
and we're visualizing
the worst-case scenario,

00:56:49.330 --> 00:56:53.298 align:middle line:90%
the power of our vision is huge.

00:56:53.298 --> 00:56:55.840 align:middle line:84%
And what I found is that people
who live in the miracles zone

00:56:55.840 --> 00:56:59.440 align:middle line:84%
use that extraordinary
power of our minds

00:56:59.440 --> 00:57:02.560 align:middle line:90%
to visualize to the positive.

00:57:02.560 --> 00:57:04.180 align:middle line:84%
They visualize what
it is they want

00:57:04.180 --> 00:57:05.590 align:middle line:90%
to have happen during the day.

00:57:05.590 --> 00:57:07.930 align:middle line:84%
They visualize the
miracles happening.

00:57:07.930 --> 00:57:09.520 align:middle line:90%
They use that power in that way.

00:57:09.520 --> 00:57:11.492 align:middle line:84%
And I know you've used
this a lot in your life.

00:57:11.492 --> 00:57:13.450 align:middle line:84%
Can I do another little
demonstration with you?

00:57:13.450 --> 00:57:13.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:57:13.900 --> 00:57:15.900 align:middle line:84%
I was just going to share
a quick story, though.

00:57:15.900 --> 00:57:17.200 align:middle line:90%
This is one of the ways that--

00:57:17.200 --> 00:57:18.820 align:middle line:84%
my father has been
very, very sick.

00:57:18.820 --> 00:57:20.830 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
things that we just

